The '''Endor shield generator bunker''' was an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] outpost on the forest moon of [[Endor/Legends|Endor]]. It was composed of the [[Death Star II/Legends|Death Star II's]] [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|deflector shield generator]], a large landing pad, a bunker, a front entrance, and a secret back entrance. The ground portion of the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]] was fought around the secret entrance.

==Characteristics==
{{Quote|The main entrance to the control bunker's on the far side of that landing platform. This isn't gonna be easy.|Leia Organa Solo|<ref name="SWE6" />}}
The base was large and had a landing pad capable of holding at least two [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|Lambda-class T-4a shuttles]]. It was at least 22.5 meters off the ground, as an [[All Terrain Armored Transport/Legends|All Terrain Armored Transport]] of [[Tempest Force/Legends|Tempest Force]], the security detail of the bunker, ''[[Tempest 1]]'', was shorter than it. The landing pad's support structure contained several catwalks underneath, connected to the top of the pad by [[Turbolift/Legends|elevators]]. The catwalks acted as docks for the AT-AT. On one side of the landing pad was the main entrance.<ref name="SWE6" />

[[File:EndorBunker-ROTJ.png|thumb|left|220px|The back door of the shield generator bunker]]
The base contained a back door that lead to a small bunker. It was built into a hill with a small clearing in front of it, and had [[Blast door/Legends|blast doors]]. The bunker consisted of a maze of long corridors that eventually led down into the main power control room, which was garrisoned by [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] and several [[Death Star Trooper/Legends|Death Star troopers]] under [[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Hewex/Legends|Hewex]], [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Grond (Imperial)|Grond]], and [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] [[Dyer/Legends|Dyer's]] command. The control room itself contained a row of computers, a screen on one of the walls, and two entry-points; one leading to the bunker hallways and the other to the generator room. The generator room was about two stories from the base of the generators to the ceiling, and was looked over by a small catwalk with a railing.<ref name="Rogue Squadron III">''[[Star Wars: Rogue Squadron III: Rebel Strike]]''</ref><ref name="SWE6" />

==History==
{{Quote|Commander Jerjerrod, should the Rebels manage to blow up the shield generator, you will turn this battle station onto the Endor Moon and destroy it.|Palpatine to Tiaan Jerjerrod|<ref name="ROTJ Novel">[[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode VI: Return of the Jedi'' novel]]</ref>}}
===Construction===
[[File:Breaking_Ground.png|thumb|350px|Vader supervising the construction]]
When the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] needed a new construction site for the second [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]], the Forest [[Moon/Legends|Moon]] of [[Endor/Legends|Endor]] was chosen.<ref name="Gamer">[[Star Wars Gamer 9|''Star Wars Gamer'' 9]]</ref> The bunker began construction sometime between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]] on the site of the [[Dulok Swamp]] of [[Gorneesh's tribe]], with many of the [[Dulok]]s being put into slave labor for its construction.<ref name="Star Wars: Ewoks—Shadows of Endor">''[[Star Wars: Ewoks—Shadows of Endor]]''</ref> [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]], as well as some of the [[Palpatine/Legends|Emperor's]] [[Emperor's Royal Guard|Royal Guards]] personally oversaw the construction of the bunker.<ref name="Breaking Ground">[[:File:Breaking_Ground.png|Breaking Ground: Imperial Base, Moon of Endor]] [[Celebration VI]] print by [[Dave Dorman]]</ref>

When Imperial teams arrived to construct the bunker's [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|deflector shield generator]] complex and other installations, they discovered [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Junas Turner]], who had come to the moon to locate the new Death Star. He was taken captive and sent to the automated prison station [[Balis-Baurgh]], along with an [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] named [[Grael]]. They would later escape, but were too late to inform the Rebellion of the threat.<ref name="Escape from Balis-Baurgh">{{JournalCite|1|Escape from Balis-Baurgh}}</ref>

===The Battle of Endor===
{{Main|Battle of Endor/Legends}}
{{Quote|You Rebel scum!|Renz, to [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="SWE6" />}}
[[File:Endor_Imperial_Platform_ST.png|thumb|250px|The Imperial outpost on Endor]]
In around 3&ndash;[[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="NEC" /> a Rebel Alliance strike team, led by [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], captured information from the cruiser ''[[Suprosa]]'' at [[Kothlis/Legends|Kothlis]]. It confirmed the existence of a second Death Star, and provided it and the shield generator bunker's location. It was not realized then, but [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] had purposely allowed the plans to be captured, so that the Rebels could be coaxed into a trap.<ref name="SOTE">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (novel)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' novel]]</ref> In order to ensure that the Rebels couldn't disable the shield generator before the Rebel fleet arrived, Palpatine made sure that a unit, [[Tempest Force/Legends|Tempest Force]], was created via the best of the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial Army]], [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Navy]], and [[Stormtrooper Corps/Legends|Stormtrooper Corps]] to guard the generator, with its size also being comparable to that of a stormtrooper legion, anticipating the possibility of a strike team being sent to infiltrate the moon.<ref name="SWE6" />

The Rebel fleet amassed near [[Sullust/Legends|Sullust]] and formulated a plan to destroy the Death Star II. A [[Endor strike team/Legends|Rebel strike team]], lead by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] was to infiltrate the moon and destroy the shield generator bunker, leaving the Death Star defenseless, while the [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|fleet]], commanded by [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Gial Ackbar]], and a substantial starfighter force led by General [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]], would jump to Endor through [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] and attack the shieldless, incomplete Death Star.<ref name="SWE6" />

Han and his commando team were joined by [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], Luke Skywalker, [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]]. They used the stolen Imperial shuttle [[Tydirium/Legends|''Tydirium'']] to slip past Imperial defenses and land on the moon, where they met the [[Bright Tree Village/Legends|Bright Tree Village]] [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]] tribe, who agreed to help the Rebels in their fight against the Imperials on Endor.<ref name="SWE6" />

Skywalker, fearing that his presence would endanger their mission, abandoned the team and allowed himself to be captured by [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Igar/Legends|Igar]], who brought him to Darth Vader on the shield generator's landing platform. In the platform's catwalks, Luke pleaded with Vader to come back to the light side, but Vader resisted, refusing to betray his master, Palpatine. Vader and Luke left Endor, the former taking the latter to Palpatine aboard the Death Star. Several hours later, Ewok scouts led the strike team to a ridge overlooking the shield generator's landing platform. On the advice of an Ewok, [[Wicket Wystri Warrick/Legends|Wicket Wystri Warrick]], the team then made their way the secret entrance, which only had four scout troopers guarding it. Another Ewok, [[Paploo/Legends|Paploo]], stole a [[74-Z speeder bike/Legends|speeder bike]], leading to three of the four guards giving chase. Solo grabbed the attention of the last guard, who chased him around the side of the bunker's entrance, where the rest of the Rebels were waiting, aiming their guns at the trooper. The guard surrendered, with his uniform being taken by Rebel [[Nik Sant/Legends|Nik Sant]], who took up the guard's post while the team went into the bunker.<ref name="SWE6" />

[[File:KilledStormtroopers.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Stormtroopers after engaging the Rebels in a firefight in the bunker's hallways]]
They met a [[Squad/Legends|squad]] of stormtroopers in one of the hallways and two sides engaged in a firefight. The stormtroopers were all killed and the Rebels sustained only minimal casualties. The Rebels continued onward made their way to the control room. They entered and forced the Imperial personnel, including Major Hewex, against the wall, while they began preparing to set [[Proton grenade/Legends|charges]]. As part of the Emperor's trap, the rest of Tempest Force was ready for them and began entering the bunker. The first to arrive, Colonel Dyer, attempted to confront the Rebels, but Han threw a charge at him, knocking him over a railing into the generator room below, resulting in his death. The rest of the Imperials, lead by Lieutenant Renz arrived and captured the Rebels. Above the moon, the fleet arrived but could not attack the Death Star as the shield was still up. Calrissian noticed and ordered their fighters to pull up,<ref name="SWE6" /> which most did, although a few didn't make it in time and crashed into the shield.<ref name="ROTJ Novel" /> A massive Imperial fleet revealed itself from behind the far side of the moon and began to launch fighters.<ref name="SWE6" />

On the Death Star, as Luke was brought before the Emperor, Palpatine contacted the station's commander, [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Tiaan Jerjerrod/Legends|Tiaan Jerjerrod]] and ordered him to fire the [[Superlaser/Legends|superlaser]] at the moon in the event that the Rebels managed to destroy the shield generator bunker.<ref name="ROTJ Novel" />

[[File:ShieldGeneratorBunkerDeath.png|thumb|250px|The destruction of the shield generator bunker]]
As the Rebels were being led out of the bunker. The Ewoks, with help from an impromptu distraction from C-3PO and R2-D2, attacked the Imperials, and the Rebels took advantage of the confusion while chaos ensued. A group of Imperial officers sealed themselves in the bunker and R2 took a blaster bolt while trying to open the doors. Han attempted to hot-wire the system, but only managed to close the blast doors by accident. Meanwhile, Chewbacca and two Ewoks captured an AT-ST and brought it to the bunker's entrance. Han, dressed in a stolen Imperial uniform and posing as Major [[Marquand/Legends|Marquand]], contacted the bunker's control room through the walker and told Hewex that the Rebels were fleeing and that the Imperials needed help pursuing them. Hewex fell for the trick and ordered the back door to be opened to allow three squads to help. As the Imperials exited the bunker, they were quickly surrounded by Rebel forces and promptly surrendered.<ref name="SWE6" />

Solo and his team entered the bunker, laid the explosive charges, and set the timer. While they hurriedly ran out of the bunker, Imperial [[Storm commando/Legends|Storm commando]] [[Sarkli]] tried to stop Solo from escaping, but ended up shot near the entrance.<ref name="Rogue Squadron III" /> Solo continued out of the bunker and took cover shortly before it exploded, destroying the shield generator and allowing the Rebel fleet to begin their assault on the Death Star.<ref name="SWE6" />

When the personnel in the [[Death Star command center|Death Star's control room]] realized that the deflector shield was down and were unable to contact the shield bunker, Jerjerrod was informed and reluctantly gave the order to fire on the moon. However, the Death Star exploded before it could do so.<ref name="ROTJ Novel" />

===Remains===
{{Quote|Guess we won the war after all.|An unidentified rebel trooper upon seeing the remains of the shield generator bunker|<ref name="Marooned">{{Tales|22|Marooned}}</ref>}}
Thirteen [[Standard month/Legends|months]] after the battle, in [[5 ABY/Legends|5 ABY]], [[Unidentified Rebel trooper (Endor)|one of the strike team members]] and a [[Unidentified scout trooper (Endor)|scout trooper]], both of whom had been marooned on Endor since the battle, came across the remains of the shield generator bunker. Having not previously known who won the battle, the destroyed shield generator confirmed to them that the Rebels had managed to win.<ref name="Marooned" />

==Behind the scenes==
The set for the Endor shield generator bunker was at an area near the Smith River's redwood forests. In 2010, the staff for ''Star Wars Insider'' tried to relocate this area at the request of longtime ''Star Wars'' fan Brandon Alinger, but the trek became elusive. They later detailed this trek in the article "[[The Hunt for Endor's Forest Moon]]," included in issue 122 of the magazine.

At [[Wikipedia:Disney Hollywood Studios|Disney Hollywood Studios]] theme park in [[Wikipedia:Florida|Florida]], a replica of the shield generator bunker serves as the backdrop for the stage that is home to the ''[[Jedi Training Academy]]'' attraction.

The shield bunker appears both in the Leia Organa and Darth Vader campaigns in the [[2001]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds]]''. The Darth Vader Battle of Endor mission is an alternate-history scenario, while the Leia Organa mission contradicts the film. The bunker has also been reimagined in LEGO form in the [[2006]] video game ''[[LEGO Star Wars II: The Original Trilogy]]''.

The bunker also serves as the location for the battle in the alternate-history scenario given in the ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II]]'' Endor downloadable content. Darth Vader's [[Dark Apprentice]] hunted down and killed Leia Organa, the last of the Jedi.

